The paper proposes a novel deep learning approach for solving the inverse problem in diffuse optical tomography, which involves the non-linear physics of photon migration in turbid media. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories, as well as the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of integral equations, which suggests that it may also belong to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category. Finally, the paper applies the method to live animals, indicating that it may also belong to the bioinformatics (cs.BIO) sub-category.
